<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../524/18524.xml">
Latin America</link></categorization>
</activity>
</psychological_feature>
</situation>
</act>
</sphere>
</state>
</event>
</grouping>
</environment>
n <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../473/142473.xml">
plantation</link>s. Also the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../225/74225.xml">
chili</link> / <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../011/113011.xml">
paprika</link> from South America was introduced in <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../533/14533.xml">
India</link></country>
 by the Portuguese and it is today an inseparable part of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../809/227809.xml">
Indian cuisine</link>.</p>
<p>

Before the Columbian Exchange, there were no <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../440/4984440.xml">
orange</link>s in <symbol wordnetid="106806469" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
